text: Roger William Jepsen (December 23, 1928 - November 13, 2020) was an American politician from the state of Iowa. A Republican, he served in the United States Senate and as Lieutenant Governor of Iowa. He was born in Cedar Falls, Iowa. Jepsen died on November 13, 2020 in Davenport, Iowa at the age of 91. ==References== ==Other websites== * * Category:1928 births Category:2020 deaths Category:People from Cedar Falls, Iowa Category:Lieutenant Governors of Iowa Category:United States senators from Iowa Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians Category:Disease-related deaths in Iowa
